******
[1] France: Aquitaine, Midi-Pyrenees
Date: October 2011
Source: European Plant Protection Organisation (EPPO) Reporting
Service 10/2011/226 [edited]
http://archives.eppo.org/EPPOReporting/2011/Rse-1110.pdf


_Plum pox virus_ detected in Aquitaine and Midi-Pyrenees
--------------------------------------------------------
The NPPO [National Plant Protection Organisation] of France recently
informed EPPO [European Plant Protection Organisation] of the
detection of _Plum pox virus_ (family _Potyviridae_; PPV - EPPO A2
List) in Aquitaine and Midi-Pyrenees. The presence of PPV was detected
for the 1st time in a nursery in Midi-Pyrenees region. Tracing-back
studies showed that the PPV-infected material originated from another
nursery in Aquitaine region, which was also found to be infected.

Further investigations will be carried out to determine the original
source of this infection. Both nurseries were producing propagation
material for the national and local markets, and no material belonging
to the infested lots has been exported outside France. Phytosanitary
measures are currently being taken: plant destruction, withdrawal of
plant passports for the production sites concerned (that is, all plots
with propagation material of _Prunus_ within a radius of 1000 m [0.6
mi] around the infected plot) for a minimum period of 3 years,
intensive surveys in _Prunus_ growing plots within a radius of 2500 m
[1.5 mi] around the infected sites and testing of asymptomatic
plants.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

